<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08075f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08075f">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08075f"> 75(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Love love to love love</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There is one manner of forming verbs from nouns and vice versa &hellip; namely that of making them exactly like one another &hellip; noun: <i>love loves</i> &mdash; <i>sleep sleeps</i>, verb: <i>love loves</i>&mdash;<i>sleep sleeps</i>, &hellip; (the lover loves; the lovers love) <small> Otto Jespersen, <a name="OJGS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#OJGS"><cite title="source">The Growth and Structure of the English Language</cite></a>, 4th ed. (Jul 1923) 160-1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
